WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:00.992 align:middle line:90%


00:00:00.992 --> 00:00:03.472 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:00:03.472 --> 00:01:06.060 align:middle line:90%


00:01:06.060 --> 00:01:09.360 align:middle line:84%
>> From his very beginnings,
man has had to live with this

00:01:09.360 --> 00:01:10.920 align:middle line:90%
rather curious substance.

00:01:10.920 --> 00:01:15.980 align:middle line:90%


00:01:15.980 --> 00:01:21.810 align:middle line:84%
It is not like wood or the earth
or the rock which shape it.

00:01:21.810 --> 00:01:24.190 align:middle line:90%
It is elusive.

00:01:24.190 --> 00:01:28.670 align:middle line:84%
It can neither be held
nor given a shape.

00:01:28.670 --> 00:01:32.210 align:middle line:84%
It is free, but man is
not free to ignore it.

00:01:32.210 --> 00:01:43.920 align:middle line:90%


00:01:43.920 --> 00:01:47.970 align:middle line:84%
>> Man can come down from the
mountain, leave his rocky cave,

00:01:47.970 --> 00:01:51.640 align:middle line:84%
turn his back on the forest, but
he cannot afford to walk away

00:01:51.640 --> 00:01:52.440 align:middle line:90%
from water.

00:01:52.440 --> 00:01:56.290 align:middle line:90%


00:01:56.290 --> 00:01:59.080 align:middle line:84%
Water is like a
magnet is to iron.

00:01:59.080 --> 00:02:02.690 align:middle line:84%
Communities and their animals
are irresistibly drawn to it.

00:02:02.690 --> 00:02:15.360 align:middle line:90%


00:02:15.360 --> 00:02:17.680 align:middle line:84%
>> These women belong to the
Samburu tribe in the north

00:02:17.680 --> 00:02:18.480 align:middle line:90%
of Kenya.

00:02:18.480 --> 00:02:21.880 align:middle line:90%


00:02:21.880 --> 00:02:26.610 align:middle line:84%
In their language, the Maa,
Samburu means butterfly.

00:02:26.610 --> 00:02:28.830 align:middle line:84%
Because like the
butterfly, the Samburu

00:02:28.830 --> 00:02:32.005 align:middle line:90%
never settle anywhere for long.

00:02:32.005 --> 00:02:32.805 align:middle line:90%
They are nomads.

00:02:32.805 --> 00:02:37.600 align:middle line:90%


00:02:37.600 --> 00:02:39.490 align:middle line:84%
In this small
tribe, it has always

00:02:39.490 --> 00:02:42.730 align:middle line:84%
been the women's task to find
and bring back the days water.

00:02:42.730 --> 00:03:08.860 align:middle line:90%


00:03:08.860 --> 00:03:11.590 align:middle line:84%
>> Woman is often
associated with water,

00:03:11.590 --> 00:03:13.660 align:middle line:84%
because she is the
symbol of grace.

00:03:13.660 --> 00:03:15.340 align:middle line:84%
Because she is the
symbol of fertility.

00:03:15.340 --> 00:03:18.250 align:middle line:90%


00:03:18.250 --> 00:03:20.800 align:middle line:84%
She is without doubt
best placed to understand

00:03:20.800 --> 00:03:24.250 align:middle line:84%
this mysterious substance,
which like her, gives

00:03:24.250 --> 00:03:29.800 align:middle line:84%
life, hence the
widely accepted idea

00:03:29.800 --> 00:03:35.160 align:middle line:84%
that water is the great
mother of the universe.

00:03:35.160 --> 00:03:39.330 align:middle line:84%
The prime element at the
origin of all things.

00:03:39.330 --> 00:03:57.900 align:middle line:90%


00:03:57.900 --> 00:04:01.200 align:middle line:90%
>> Water is energy, a dynamic.

00:04:01.200 --> 00:04:02.760 align:middle line:90%
Always moving.

00:04:02.760 --> 00:04:03.630 align:middle line:90%
Always changing.

00:04:03.630 --> 00:04:11.450 align:middle line:90%


00:04:11.450 --> 00:04:13.790 align:middle line:84%
Once it has birthed from
the depths of the earth,

00:04:13.790 --> 00:04:16.339 align:middle line:84%
it chooses its way, and
nothing can stop it.

00:04:16.339 --> 00:04:24.550 align:middle line:90%


00:04:24.550 --> 00:04:26.890 align:middle line:90%
It carves the land.

00:04:26.890 --> 00:04:28.725 align:middle line:90%
It creates the landscape.

00:04:28.725 --> 00:04:31.460 align:middle line:90%


00:04:31.460 --> 00:04:33.700 align:middle line:84%
Indeed, in Chinese,
the word landscape

00:04:33.700 --> 00:04:37.570 align:middle line:84%
is Chen Shui, which means
literally the mountain

00:04:37.570 --> 00:04:38.370 align:middle line:90%
and the water.

00:04:38.370 --> 00:04:46.940 align:middle line:90%


00:04:46.940 --> 00:04:50.450 align:middle line:84%
Men have always been fascinated
by this element, which

00:04:50.450 --> 00:04:54.290 align:middle line:84%
is peaceful at one remote
and turbulent the next.

00:04:54.290 --> 00:04:57.260 align:middle line:84%
The mirror of heaven
or the clamor of hell.

00:04:57.260 --> 00:05:11.590 align:middle line:90%


00:05:11.590 --> 00:05:16.240 align:middle line:84%
>> Water has always
inspired the imagination.

00:05:16.240 --> 00:05:19.390 align:middle line:84%
In its wildest state,
it expresses itself

00:05:19.390 --> 00:05:20.690 align:middle line:90%
as a living entity.

00:05:20.690 --> 00:05:21.490 align:middle line:90%
Powerful.

00:05:21.490 --> 00:05:23.605 align:middle line:90%


00:05:23.605 --> 00:05:24.405 align:middle line:90%
Superior.

00:05:24.405 --> 00:05:34.890 align:middle line:90%


00:05:34.890 --> 00:05:38.610 align:middle line:84%
But at the foot of the cascade,
water is no longer the same.

00:05:38.610 --> 00:05:41.650 align:middle line:90%


00:05:41.650 --> 00:05:45.870 align:middle line:84%
The violent rush has
turned into vapor.

00:05:45.870 --> 00:05:48.630 align:middle line:90%
Fury into silk like evanescence.

00:05:48.630 --> 00:05:52.050 align:middle line:90%


00:05:52.050 --> 00:05:56.280 align:middle line:84%
>> Baffled by such changes,
man, instead of creating one god

00:05:56.280 --> 00:06:02.670 align:middle line:84%
of water, has invented many,
each connected to one form

00:06:02.670 --> 00:06:04.410 align:middle line:84%
or another of the
liquid element.

00:06:04.410 --> 00:06:08.450 align:middle line:90%


00:06:08.450 --> 00:06:14.360 align:middle line:84%
Spirit of springs, god of the
sea, or goddess of the river.

00:06:14.360 --> 00:06:17.030 align:middle line:84%
It is everyday life and the
environment which decide.

00:06:17.030 --> 00:06:20.870 align:middle line:90%


00:06:20.870 --> 00:06:22.670 align:middle line:84%
All the peoples
who depend on water

00:06:22.670 --> 00:06:25.010 align:middle line:84%
for their survival
and their crops

00:06:25.010 --> 00:06:28.130 align:middle line:84%
invented rain gods as
their first gods of water.

00:06:28.130 --> 00:06:37.060 align:middle line:90%


00:06:37.060 --> 00:06:40.640 align:middle line:84%
>> In China, they took
the form of dragon gods.

00:06:40.640 --> 00:06:43.015 align:middle line:84%
They were called Longwang, Ao
Guang, Ao Shun, and Ao Qin.

00:06:43.015 --> 00:06:47.890 align:middle line:90%


00:06:47.890 --> 00:06:51.250 align:middle line:84%
Astride their fearsome
beasts, they roamed the skies,

00:06:51.250 --> 00:06:52.950 align:middle line:90%
dragging the clouds behind them.

00:06:52.950 --> 00:06:55.650 align:middle line:90%


00:06:55.650 --> 00:06:57.990 align:middle line:10%
The gods brought their
precious gift to the sky

00:06:57.990 --> 00:07:01.665 align:middle line:10%
above the crops, and each
year, the miracle was repeated.

00:07:01.665 --> 00:07:04.800 align:middle line:90%


00:07:04.800 --> 00:07:08.860 align:middle line:84%
The rain started
to fall and work

00:07:08.860 --> 00:07:10.435 align:middle line:84%
could carry on in
the paddy fields.

00:07:10.435 --> 00:07:17.600 align:middle line:90%


00:07:17.600 --> 00:07:19.460 align:middle line:84%
>> In countries where
there is monsoon,

00:07:19.460 --> 00:07:22.730 align:middle line:84%
the rain returns inevitably
with the seasons,

00:07:22.730 --> 00:07:25.385 align:middle line:84%
and the gods tend to be
more fanciful, more joyful.

00:07:25.385 --> 00:07:28.280 align:middle line:90%


00:07:28.280 --> 00:07:30.170 align:middle line:84%
But the gods have
quite a different image

00:07:30.170 --> 00:07:33.470 align:middle line:84%
in arid climates, where
life really depends

00:07:33.470 --> 00:07:34.760 align:middle line:90%
on the moods of the sky.

00:07:34.760 --> 00:07:42.900 align:middle line:90%


00:07:42.900 --> 00:07:45.810 align:middle line:84%
In pre Columbian America,
the Maya's rain god

00:07:45.810 --> 00:07:46.980 align:middle line:90%
was called Chaac.

00:07:46.980 --> 00:07:51.370 align:middle line:90%


00:07:51.370 --> 00:07:53.680 align:middle line:84%
He was represented
by a mask carved

00:07:53.680 --> 00:07:56.530 align:middle line:84%
into monuments, which can
still be seen in Mexico

00:07:56.530 --> 00:07:57.850 align:middle line:90%
on the Yucatan Peninsula.

00:07:57.850 --> 00:08:06.320 align:middle line:90%


00:08:06.320 --> 00:08:09.590 align:middle line:10%
>> The image of Chaac
is quite abstract,

00:08:09.590 --> 00:08:12.620 align:middle line:10%
and it isn't always easy for
the layman to identify him

00:08:12.620 --> 00:08:16.040 align:middle line:10%
on the ruined stones
of Mayan architecture.

00:08:16.040 --> 00:08:18.200 align:middle line:84%
The simplest way
to recognize him

00:08:18.200 --> 00:08:22.710 align:middle line:84%
is to look for the carved
stones jutting out of the walls.

00:08:22.710 --> 00:08:25.490 align:middle line:90%
These represent his hooked nose.

00:08:25.490 --> 00:08:28.610 align:middle line:84%
>> The sheer number of these
masks shows the extent to which

00:08:28.610 --> 00:08:31.900 align:middle line:84%
the Maya's were preoccupied
with the water god,

00:08:31.900 --> 00:08:34.829 align:middle line:84%
for they were an agricultural
people living in a region where

00:08:34.829 --> 00:08:35.629 align:middle line:90%
water is scarce.

00:08:35.629 --> 00:08:41.309 align:middle line:90%


00:08:41.309 --> 00:08:45.630 align:middle line:84%
It collects at the bottom of
natural wells called cenotes,

00:08:45.630 --> 00:08:46.845 align:middle line:90%
which serve as water systems.

00:08:46.845 --> 00:08:59.500 align:middle line:90%


00:08:59.500 --> 00:09:01.150 align:middle line:84%
These cavities,
which were caused

00:09:01.150 --> 00:09:03.730 align:middle line:84%
by the collapse of the
calcareous cave roof,

00:09:03.730 --> 00:09:06.040 align:middle line:84%
were thought by the Maya's
to be the empty chambers

00:09:06.040 --> 00:09:07.270 align:middle line:90%
of the kingdom of Chaac.

00:09:07.270 --> 00:09:15.510 align:middle line:90%


00:09:15.510 --> 00:09:17.820 align:middle line:84%
>> They believed that to
maintain the water level

00:09:17.820 --> 00:09:20.940 align:middle line:84%
in the cenotes, they had to
keep the god happy and make

00:09:20.940 --> 00:09:22.110 align:middle line:90%
sacrifices to him.

00:09:22.110 --> 00:09:27.360 align:middle line:90%


00:09:27.360 --> 00:09:31.230 align:middle line:84%
In this little building on
the site of Chichen Itza,

00:09:31.230 --> 00:09:35.550 align:middle line:84%
children were purified
before being drowned nearby

00:09:35.550 --> 00:09:38.875 align:middle line:84%
in the green waters
of the sacred cenotes.

00:09:38.875 --> 00:09:53.450 align:middle line:90%


00:09:53.450 --> 00:09:56.420 align:middle line:84%
>> Believing that the rain
god lived in the underworld,

00:09:56.420 --> 00:09:59.750 align:middle line:84%
the Maya's wanted
to be closer to him,

00:09:59.750 --> 00:10:01.885 align:middle line:84%
so they worshiped him
in underground caves.

00:10:01.885 --> 00:10:07.120 align:middle line:90%


00:10:07.120 --> 00:10:11.320 align:middle line:84%
Here, they saw signs of
his presence everywhere.

00:10:11.320 --> 00:10:13.630 align:middle line:84%
Droplets of water on
the tips of stalactites

00:10:13.630 --> 00:10:15.930 align:middle line:84%
were for them the
tears of the god.

00:10:15.930 --> 00:10:29.290 align:middle line:90%


00:10:29.290 --> 00:10:31.960 align:middle line:10%
In the caves of
Balankanche, [INAUDIBLE]

00:10:31.960 --> 00:10:36.077 align:middle line:84%
have been found carved with
the effigy of the god, Chaac.

00:10:36.077 --> 00:10:37.660 align:middle line:84%
They are still laying
where the Maya's

00:10:37.660 --> 00:10:39.210 align:middle line:90%
used to assemble for prayer.

00:10:39.210 --> 00:10:47.110 align:middle line:90%


00:10:47.110 --> 00:10:52.240 align:middle line:84%
>> In Africa to bring rain, the
Dogon's of Mali pray to Ama,

00:10:52.240 --> 00:10:53.170 align:middle line:90%
their great deity.

00:10:53.170 --> 00:10:54.931 align:middle line:90%
[SONG CHANTING]

00:10:54.931 --> 00:11:08.692 align:middle line:90%


00:11:08.692 --> 00:11:11.380 align:middle line:84%
The representation
of this posture

00:11:11.380 --> 00:11:13.190 align:middle line:90%
is characteristic of their art.

00:11:13.190 --> 00:11:21.950 align:middle line:90%


00:11:21.950 --> 00:11:25.430 align:middle line:84%
>> When water is scarce, its
presence is often considered

00:11:25.430 --> 00:11:27.215 align:middle line:84%
as proof of the
benevolence of the gods.

00:11:27.215 --> 00:11:32.570 align:middle line:90%


00:11:32.570 --> 00:11:35.870 align:middle line:90%
Water allows man to exist.

00:11:35.870 --> 00:11:38.480 align:middle line:84%
It is evidence of the
power of the gods over men.

00:11:38.480 --> 00:11:43.380 align:middle line:90%


00:11:43.380 --> 00:11:46.200 align:middle line:84%
And we hear it like a litany
in the rhythmic chants

00:11:46.200 --> 00:11:47.160 align:middle line:90%
to which they work.

00:11:47.160 --> 00:11:50.082 align:middle line:90%
[SONG CHANTING]

00:11:50.082 --> 00:12:02.270 align:middle line:90%


00:12:02.270 --> 00:12:06.170 align:middle line:84%
>> The sacred nature of water
is often inseparable from its

00:12:06.170 --> 00:12:07.010 align:middle line:90%
practical aspect.

00:12:07.010 --> 00:12:13.920 align:middle line:90%


00:12:13.920 --> 00:12:18.750 align:middle line:84%
Families, clans, tribes have
always gathered together

00:12:18.750 --> 00:12:22.830 align:middle line:84%
where water is
available to be used

00:12:22.830 --> 00:12:24.760 align:middle line:90%
for the tasks of everyday life.

00:12:24.760 --> 00:12:38.170 align:middle line:90%


00:12:38.170 --> 00:12:40.720 align:middle line:84%
>> In the Ivory
Coast near Abidjan,

00:12:40.720 --> 00:12:43.660 align:middle line:84%
this branch of the river Banco
has become a sort of great wash

00:12:43.660 --> 00:12:44.460 align:middle line:90%
area.

00:12:44.460 --> 00:12:49.200 align:middle line:90%


00:12:49.200 --> 00:12:52.920 align:middle line:84%
A veritable community
has formed here.

00:12:52.920 --> 00:12:56.070 align:middle line:84%
With its hierarchy,
its clans, its codes.

00:12:56.070 --> 00:13:14.900 align:middle line:90%


00:13:14.900 --> 00:13:17.735 align:middle line:84%
>> Water creates and
maintains a social bond.

00:13:17.735 --> 00:13:25.790 align:middle line:90%


00:13:25.790 --> 00:13:28.760 align:middle line:84%
This same water is
their playground.

00:13:28.760 --> 00:13:30.140 align:middle line:90%
They share it.

00:13:30.140 --> 00:13:32.810 align:middle line:84%
They take it with one
hand, they leave it

00:13:32.810 --> 00:13:36.860 align:middle line:84%
for someone else without
a second thought.

00:13:36.860 --> 00:13:38.600 align:middle line:90%
It belongs to no one.

00:13:38.600 --> 00:13:40.260 align:middle line:90%
It belongs to everyone.

00:13:40.260 --> 00:13:47.120 align:middle line:90%


00:13:47.120 --> 00:13:50.330 align:middle line:84%
Here, water is an
everyday element,

00:13:50.330 --> 00:13:51.920 align:middle line:84%
but it is what brings
people together.

00:13:51.920 --> 00:14:00.000 align:middle line:90%


00:14:00.000 --> 00:14:03.510 align:middle line:84%
>> Water is never
a simple substance.

00:14:03.510 --> 00:14:07.810 align:middle line:84%
It is, at the same time,
familiar and mysterious.

00:14:07.810 --> 00:14:09.810 align:middle line:84%
It takes us beyond
mere appearance.

00:14:09.810 --> 00:14:14.770 align:middle line:90%


00:14:14.770 --> 00:14:16.870 align:middle line:84%
Behind its prosaic
character, there

00:14:16.870 --> 00:14:19.900 align:middle line:90%
is often another dimension.

00:14:19.900 --> 00:14:25.240 align:middle line:84%
Images, a symbolism, an
almost universal symbolism.

00:14:25.240 --> 00:14:32.040 align:middle line:90%


00:14:32.040 --> 00:14:36.760 align:middle line:84%
>> This clay tablet dates
from the 7th century BC.

00:14:36.760 --> 00:14:40.360 align:middle line:84%
It was found in Mesopotamia
in the archives of the King

00:14:40.360 --> 00:14:42.550 align:middle line:90%
Ashurbanipal.

00:14:42.550 --> 00:14:45.720 align:middle line:84%
It recounts the
Epic of Gilgamesh,

00:14:45.720 --> 00:14:48.260 align:middle line:84%
a tale famous throughout the
whole of the ancient orient.

00:14:48.260 --> 00:14:50.910 align:middle line:90%


00:14:50.910 --> 00:14:54.860 align:middle line:10%
>> These cuneiform characters
tell the story of a flood

00:14:54.860 --> 00:14:58.800 align:middle line:10%
and of a hero who escaped the
fury of the waters by building

00:14:58.800 --> 00:15:01.650 align:middle line:10%
a boat.

00:15:01.650 --> 00:15:04.760 align:middle line:84%
It is the story of Noah
well before the Bible story.

00:15:04.760 --> 00:15:16.010 align:middle line:90%


00:15:16.010 --> 00:15:18.630 align:middle line:84%
>> The story of the flood
is present in nearly all

00:15:18.630 --> 00:15:23.660 align:middle line:84%
of the mythologies of the
world, China, India, Africa,

00:15:23.660 --> 00:15:28.520 align:middle line:84%
Polynesia, in pre
Colombian America.

00:15:28.520 --> 00:15:32.990 align:middle line:84%
It's always more or
less the same story.

00:15:32.990 --> 00:15:36.830 align:middle line:84%
Men have offended the
gods, and to punish them

00:15:36.830 --> 00:15:39.980 align:middle line:84%
the gods decide to cover
the Earth with water

00:15:39.980 --> 00:15:41.495 align:middle line:84%
and drown them
beneath the waves.

00:15:41.495 --> 00:15:54.360 align:middle line:90%


00:15:54.360 --> 00:15:58.010 align:middle line:84%
>> The drowning of men
to pay for his sins.

00:15:58.010 --> 00:16:00.040 align:middle line:84%
It's one of the oldest
metaphors in the world.

00:16:00.040 --> 00:16:08.080 align:middle line:90%


00:16:08.080 --> 00:16:10.510 align:middle line:84%
When they imagine
divine punishment,

00:16:10.510 --> 00:16:13.450 align:middle line:84%
people often refer to
the flooding of rivers.

00:16:13.450 --> 00:16:15.000 align:middle line:90%
Inundation.

00:16:15.000 --> 00:16:17.230 align:middle line:84%
All the delusional
catastrophes etched

00:16:17.230 --> 00:16:18.390 align:middle line:90%
in their collective memory.

00:16:18.390 --> 00:16:27.730 align:middle line:90%


00:16:27.730 --> 00:16:30.470 align:middle line:84%
>> Water is the favorite
weapon of angry gods.

00:16:30.470 --> 00:16:38.600 align:middle line:90%


00:16:38.600 --> 00:16:43.280 align:middle line:84%
This raging torrent is also
endowed with positive virtues.

00:16:43.280 --> 00:16:47.790 align:middle line:84%
It washes away the
misdeeds of the world.

00:16:47.790 --> 00:16:50.640 align:middle line:84%
It comes to punish
man, but it also

00:16:50.640 --> 00:16:55.060 align:middle line:84%
comes to cleanse the earth to
prepare it for a new beginning.

00:16:55.060 --> 00:17:00.560 align:middle line:90%


00:17:00.560 --> 00:17:03.200 align:middle line:84%
>> The notion of a purifying
flood is very prevalent

00:17:03.200 --> 00:17:04.520 align:middle line:90%
in Hindu mythology.

00:17:04.520 --> 00:17:07.760 align:middle line:90%


00:17:07.760 --> 00:17:09.350 align:middle line:90%
It concerns mainly the Ganges.

00:17:09.350 --> 00:17:12.500 align:middle line:90%


00:17:12.500 --> 00:17:15.869 align:middle line:84%
This river rises in the
heart of the Himalayas.

00:17:15.869 --> 00:17:18.515 align:middle line:84%
There, its waters are
of the utmost purity.

00:17:18.515 --> 00:17:22.900 align:middle line:90%


00:17:22.900 --> 00:17:25.089 align:middle line:84%
So pure, that they
inspired the authors

00:17:25.089 --> 00:17:28.450 align:middle line:84%
of the real manor, an epic
poet of the 6th century,

00:17:28.450 --> 00:17:30.940 align:middle line:90%
to write these lines.

00:17:30.940 --> 00:17:33.970 align:middle line:90%
May its water purify us forever.

00:17:33.970 --> 00:17:36.310 align:middle line:90%
He, the sacred river.

00:17:36.310 --> 00:17:38.350 align:middle line:90%
The destroyer and enemy of sin.

00:17:38.350 --> 00:17:49.210 align:middle line:90%


00:17:49.210 --> 00:17:51.880 align:middle line:84%
>> Downstream, by the
time it reaches Benares,

00:17:51.880 --> 00:17:56.410 align:middle line:84%
also called Varanasi, the Ganges
has lost its original impunity,

00:17:56.410 --> 00:17:59.780 align:middle line:84%
and its foul waters
flow sluggishly.

00:17:59.780 --> 00:18:02.861 align:middle line:84%
And yet, it has lost nothing
of its sacred character.

00:18:02.861 --> 00:18:10.720 align:middle line:90%


00:18:10.720 --> 00:18:14.160 align:middle line:90%
In fact, the Ganges is feminine.

00:18:14.160 --> 00:18:17.310 align:middle line:84%
She is Ganga, a
celestial divinity

00:18:17.310 --> 00:18:20.145 align:middle line:84%
that the creator is sent down
to Earth against her will.

00:18:20.145 --> 00:18:23.494 align:middle line:90%


00:18:23.494 --> 00:18:28.290 align:middle line:84%
Her unrest finally found peace
in the hair of the god Shiva.

00:18:28.290 --> 00:18:30.360 align:middle line:84%
With his snakes
and his trident, he

00:18:30.360 --> 00:18:32.460 align:middle line:84%
was charged with the
organization of the world.

00:18:32.460 --> 00:18:40.000 align:middle line:90%


00:18:40.000 --> 00:18:43.490 align:middle line:84%
>> The Ganges, flowing
over 2,700 kilometers,

00:18:43.490 --> 00:18:47.240 align:middle line:84%
may not be the longest river,
but there is no doubt it is

00:18:47.240 --> 00:18:48.080 align:middle line:90%
the most holy.

00:18:48.080 --> 00:18:55.570 align:middle line:90%


00:18:55.570 --> 00:18:57.970 align:middle line:84%
All Hindus dream of
making a pilgrimage here

00:18:57.970 --> 00:19:00.640 align:middle line:84%
to purify themselves
in the waters of Ganga

00:19:00.640 --> 00:19:02.510 align:middle line:90%
Mata, the divine mother.

00:19:02.510 --> 00:19:03.310 align:middle line:90%
Mother Ganges.

00:19:03.310 --> 00:19:13.740 align:middle line:90%


00:19:13.740 --> 00:19:17.880 align:middle line:84%
These polluted waters can
bring 1,000 diseases and death,

00:19:17.880 --> 00:19:20.070 align:middle line:84%
and yet, Indians bathe
here quite happily.

00:19:20.070 --> 00:19:27.710 align:middle line:90%


00:19:27.710 --> 00:19:30.830 align:middle line:84%
>> The color of the river and
the waste it carries are of no

00:19:30.830 --> 00:19:32.150 align:middle line:90%
importance.

00:19:32.150 --> 00:19:34.940 align:middle line:84%
In Hindu tradition, the
waters of the Ganges

00:19:34.940 --> 00:19:36.830 align:middle line:90%
have a purifying power.

00:19:36.830 --> 00:19:39.185 align:middle line:84%
To bathe in them is to
wash away all one's sins.

00:19:39.185 --> 00:19:48.260 align:middle line:90%


00:19:48.260 --> 00:19:52.200 align:middle line:84%
Here, they put into practice
the words of the poet.

00:19:52.200 --> 00:19:54.950 align:middle line:84%
Whoever washes his
body and purifies

00:19:54.950 --> 00:19:58.400 align:middle line:84%
his spirit of all the
stains of an impure age

00:19:58.400 --> 00:20:01.370 align:middle line:84%
will never again fold into
the ocean of the world,

00:20:01.370 --> 00:20:02.660 align:middle line:90%
but will achieve freedom.

00:20:02.660 --> 00:20:11.620 align:middle line:90%


00:20:11.620 --> 00:20:13.750 align:middle line:90%
All these people have one dream.

00:20:13.750 --> 00:20:16.840 align:middle line:84%
Not to be reborn
after their death.

00:20:16.840 --> 00:20:20.020 align:middle line:84%
For every life, even a
happy and prosperous one

00:20:20.020 --> 00:20:23.110 align:middle line:84%
is a burden compared
to Moksha, the nirvan

00:20:23.110 --> 00:20:26.740 align:middle line:84%
of the Hindu, the state where
the soul blends peaceably

00:20:26.740 --> 00:20:27.670 align:middle line:90%
into the universe.

00:20:27.670 --> 00:20:33.750 align:middle line:90%


00:20:33.750 --> 00:20:36.270 align:middle line:84%
The best way never
to be reincarnated

00:20:36.270 --> 00:20:40.050 align:middle line:84%
is to die here on the
banks of the great river

00:20:40.050 --> 00:20:42.270 align:middle line:84%
and to have your ashes
cast upon its waters.

00:20:42.270 --> 00:20:51.380 align:middle line:90%


00:20:51.380 --> 00:20:54.260 align:middle line:84%
>> But this dream is
not granted to everyone,

00:20:54.260 --> 00:20:56.690 align:middle line:84%
and many of the pilgrims
were returned to their towns

00:20:56.690 --> 00:20:58.610 align:middle line:84%
and homelands at the
end of their pilgrimage.

00:20:58.610 --> 00:21:07.210 align:middle line:90%


00:21:07.210 --> 00:21:09.580 align:middle line:84%
Those who can afford
it have had homes

00:21:09.580 --> 00:21:13.195 align:middle line:84%
built on the ghats, the steps
that lead down to the water.

00:21:13.195 --> 00:21:19.510 align:middle line:90%


00:21:19.510 --> 00:21:23.380 align:middle line:84%
There are sumptuous palaces
here built by the Maharajah's

00:21:23.380 --> 00:21:25.540 align:middle line:90%
in days gone by.

00:21:25.540 --> 00:21:27.490 align:middle line:84%
At the end of their
lives, they came

00:21:27.490 --> 00:21:29.440 align:middle line:84%
to live here and
wait comfortably

00:21:29.440 --> 00:21:32.275 align:middle line:84%
for the most holy of deaths
on the banks of the Ganges.

00:21:32.275 --> 00:21:53.980 align:middle line:90%


00:21:53.980 --> 00:21:56.530 align:middle line:84%
For Hindus, religion
is very closely

00:21:56.530 --> 00:21:59.530 align:middle line:90%
associated with everyday life.

00:21:59.530 --> 00:22:02.440 align:middle line:84%
There is no separation between
the holy and the profane.

00:22:02.440 --> 00:22:06.100 align:middle line:90%


00:22:06.100 --> 00:22:08.950 align:middle line:84%
>> The washing of the soul
and of the body are performed

00:22:08.950 --> 00:22:10.840 align:middle line:90%
equally and at the same time.

00:22:10.840 --> 00:22:15.610 align:middle line:90%


00:22:15.610 --> 00:22:17.640 align:middle line:90%
Water washes.

00:22:17.640 --> 00:22:18.615 align:middle line:90%
Water purifies.

00:22:18.615 --> 00:22:21.210 align:middle line:90%


00:22:21.210 --> 00:22:23.250 align:middle line:84%
Its proven physical
effectiveness--

00:22:23.250 --> 00:22:25.830 align:middle line:84%
when used on both the
body and on clothing--

00:22:25.830 --> 00:22:28.380 align:middle line:84%
has inspired prophets and
priests of all the religions

00:22:28.380 --> 00:22:29.180 align:middle line:90%
of the world.

00:22:29.180 --> 00:22:36.790 align:middle line:90%


00:22:36.790 --> 00:22:40.360 align:middle line:90%
>> Water washes away stains.

00:22:40.360 --> 00:22:42.570 align:middle line:84%
This simple image is
accessible to all.

00:22:42.570 --> 00:22:49.890 align:middle line:90%


00:22:49.890 --> 00:22:54.780 align:middle line:84%
And water is a very convenient
medium for sacred things.

00:22:54.780 --> 00:22:58.620 align:middle line:84%
It is available,
it's easy to carry.

00:22:58.620 --> 00:23:00.615 align:middle line:84%
It's the ideal
substance for rituals.

00:23:00.615 --> 00:23:07.150 align:middle line:90%


00:23:07.150 --> 00:23:10.480 align:middle line:84%
It is present in all
devotions, all ceremonies.

00:23:10.480 --> 00:23:26.570 align:middle line:90%


00:23:26.570 --> 00:23:31.130 align:middle line:84%
>> Man at prayer establishes
a relationship with his god.

00:23:31.130 --> 00:23:35.260 align:middle line:84%
By definition, the
relationship is unequal.

00:23:35.260 --> 00:23:40.740 align:middle line:84%
He must appear in his best light
out of respect, out of fear.

00:23:40.740 --> 00:23:41.885 align:middle line:90%
He must purify himself.

00:23:41.885 --> 00:23:59.790 align:middle line:90%


00:23:59.790 --> 00:24:03.070 align:middle line:84%
>> The figurative meaning is
often the basis of the literal

00:24:03.070 --> 00:24:05.620 align:middle line:90%
meaning.

00:24:05.620 --> 00:24:10.090 align:middle line:84%
When incense is burned, it is
associated with the simple idea

00:24:10.090 --> 00:24:12.700 align:middle line:84%
that the swirls of
smoke themselves

00:24:12.700 --> 00:24:16.180 align:middle line:84%
that are carrying
prayers towards the gods.

00:24:16.180 --> 00:24:19.630 align:middle line:84%
In the same way, crystal
water is the absolute symbol

00:24:19.630 --> 00:24:20.665 align:middle line:90%
of the ideal of purity.

00:24:20.665 --> 00:24:29.850 align:middle line:90%


00:24:29.850 --> 00:24:32.900 align:middle line:84%
In the second century, the
Carthaginian theologian,

00:24:32.900 --> 00:24:36.630 align:middle line:84%
Tertullian wrote,
in the beginning,

00:24:36.630 --> 00:24:40.360 align:middle line:90%
god made heaven and earth.

00:24:40.360 --> 00:24:45.630 align:middle line:10%
The darkness was still
formless, the earth unshaped.

00:24:45.630 --> 00:24:48.930 align:middle line:10%
The heavens badly human.

00:24:48.930 --> 00:24:53.190 align:middle line:84%
Water alone, a perfect substance
from the very beginning, life

00:24:53.190 --> 00:24:57.060 align:middle line:84%
giving and simple, spilled
forth its limpidity

00:24:57.060 --> 00:24:59.180 align:middle line:90%
like a throne worthy of its god.

00:24:59.180 --> 00:25:03.620 align:middle line:90%


00:25:03.620 --> 00:25:05.600 align:middle line:90%
>> Water worthy of the gods.

00:25:05.600 --> 00:25:10.570 align:middle line:90%


00:25:10.570 --> 00:25:15.640 align:middle line:84%
In Egypt, the gods were
worshipped three times a day.

00:25:15.640 --> 00:25:17.940 align:middle line:84%
Three times a day,
the priest on duty

00:25:17.940 --> 00:25:20.430 align:middle line:84%
would go to the
innermost sanctum and--

00:25:20.430 --> 00:25:22.920 align:middle line:84%
surrounded by the
whorls of incense--

00:25:22.920 --> 00:25:25.020 align:middle line:84%
would sprinkle the
ground with pure water.

00:25:25.020 --> 00:25:39.570 align:middle line:90%


00:25:39.570 --> 00:25:42.200 align:middle line:10%
This water was drawn from
the sacred lake that--

00:25:42.200 --> 00:25:43.370 align:middle line:10%
like here at Karnak--

00:25:43.370 --> 00:25:45.680 align:middle line:10%
was near the temple.

00:25:45.680 --> 00:25:49.460 align:middle line:10%
>> Here and elsewhere, religious
edifices often contained

00:25:49.460 --> 00:25:55.250 align:middle line:10%
a pool, a receptacle, or
a spring of sacred water.

00:25:55.250 --> 00:25:59.840 align:middle line:84%
In ancient Greece too, water
was part of the ritual.

00:25:59.840 --> 00:26:03.140 align:middle line:84%
As we can see at the spring
that gushes forth at Delphi,

00:26:03.140 --> 00:26:06.260 align:middle line:84%
near the temple of Pythia, one
of the most famous characters

00:26:06.260 --> 00:26:07.820 align:middle line:90%
of antiquity.

00:26:07.820 --> 00:26:11.030 align:middle line:84%
She delivered her oracles
after long ceremonies.

00:26:11.030 --> 00:26:13.490 align:middle line:10%
>> She sacrificed a goat
to ensure the goodwill

00:26:13.490 --> 00:26:17.880 align:middle line:10%
of the gods, chewed
laurel leaves,

00:26:17.880 --> 00:26:22.870 align:middle line:10%
and drank holy water from
the Castalian spring.

00:26:22.870 --> 00:26:25.360 align:middle line:10%
Once she had attained
a higher state,

00:26:25.360 --> 00:26:28.285 align:middle line:10%
she returned to her three legged
stool to predict the future.

00:26:28.285 --> 00:26:34.720 align:middle line:90%


00:26:34.720 --> 00:26:37.340 align:middle line:84%
>> We can find the same
combination of holy water,

00:26:37.340 --> 00:26:46.580 align:middle line:84%
blood sacrifice, and mystic
trance in the voodoo cult.

00:26:46.580 --> 00:26:47.480 align:middle line:90%
This cult--

00:26:47.480 --> 00:26:49.550 align:middle line:84%
as it is practiced
in southern Benin--

00:26:49.550 --> 00:26:52.100 align:middle line:84%
is the original expression
of voodoo ceremonies.

00:26:52.100 --> 00:26:56.060 align:middle line:90%


00:26:56.060 --> 00:26:58.700 align:middle line:84%
The very codified
rhythms and dances

00:26:58.700 --> 00:27:00.695 align:middle line:84%
are a means of reaching
the state of trance.

00:27:00.695 --> 00:27:10.690 align:middle line:90%


00:27:10.690 --> 00:27:14.290 align:middle line:90%
The cult incorporate sacrifices.

00:27:14.290 --> 00:27:17.920 align:middle line:84%
The blood spilt is the supreme
offering to the spirits.

00:27:17.920 --> 00:27:19.240 align:middle line:90%
It is meant to nourish them.

00:27:19.240 --> 00:27:31.630 align:middle line:90%


00:27:31.630 --> 00:27:35.470 align:middle line:84%
This is the place and the moment
when the whole community enters

00:27:35.470 --> 00:27:38.290 align:middle line:84%
into a relationship with the
powers of the other world.

00:27:38.290 --> 00:27:43.690 align:middle line:90%


00:27:43.690 --> 00:27:46.780 align:middle line:84%
>> As the bloody communion
reaches fever pitch,

00:27:46.780 --> 00:27:50.260 align:middle line:84%
women come out of the temple in
search of the one thing without

00:27:50.260 --> 00:27:53.710 align:middle line:84%
which the ceremonies would
be imperfect, worthless.

00:27:53.710 --> 00:28:04.640 align:middle line:90%


00:28:04.640 --> 00:28:07.390 align:middle line:90%
The ritual continues.

00:28:07.390 --> 00:28:12.550 align:middle line:84%
Barefoot in single file,
they walk to the holy stream

00:28:12.550 --> 00:28:14.455 align:middle line:84%
to bring back the
purifying waters.

00:28:14.455 --> 00:28:28.970 align:middle line:90%


00:28:28.970 --> 00:28:31.790 align:middle line:84%
>> The sacred pool turns out
to be no more than a simple

00:28:31.790 --> 00:28:33.290 align:middle line:90%
waterhole.

00:28:33.290 --> 00:28:36.230 align:middle line:84%
Not unusual in a region
where there are so many,

00:28:36.230 --> 00:28:39.890 align:middle line:84%
but this one is different
because men have said so.

00:28:39.890 --> 00:28:42.920 align:middle line:90%


00:28:42.920 --> 00:28:45.080 align:middle line:84%
Because they had
to decide which one

00:28:45.080 --> 00:28:47.660 align:middle line:84%
of all the ordinary
waterholes in the area

00:28:47.660 --> 00:28:50.270 align:middle line:84%
deserve to be mixed
with blood and poured

00:28:50.270 --> 00:28:52.880 align:middle line:84%
onto the ceremonial altars
made of dried earth.

00:28:52.880 --> 00:28:54.784 align:middle line:90%
[SONG CHANTING]

00:28:54.784 --> 00:28:58.600 align:middle line:90%


00:28:58.600 --> 00:29:02.180 align:middle line:90%
>> Water associated with blood.

00:29:02.180 --> 00:29:06.520 align:middle line:84%
Two vital fluids
associated with ritual.

00:29:06.520 --> 00:29:08.680 align:middle line:90%
Both have a significance.

00:29:08.680 --> 00:29:13.815 align:middle line:84%
Water for its purifying
virtues, blood for communion.

00:29:13.815 --> 00:29:15.795 align:middle line:90%
[VOCALIZING]

00:29:15.795 --> 00:29:24.210 align:middle line:90%


00:29:24.210 --> 00:29:27.180 align:middle line:90%
[SINGING IN LATIN]

00:29:27.180 --> 00:29:35.610 align:middle line:90%


00:29:35.610 --> 00:29:39.270 align:middle line:84%
>> Beyond civilisations,
beyond religions,

00:29:39.270 --> 00:29:43.160 align:middle line:84%
there is a universality
in the image itself.

00:29:43.160 --> 00:29:47.670 align:middle line:84%
Christians take the blood
of Christ in communion.

00:29:47.670 --> 00:29:52.740 align:middle line:84%
The most sacred of waters finds
here a supreme substitute.

00:29:52.740 --> 00:29:56.220 align:middle line:84%
>> Up until the death of Jesus,
water played a leading part

00:29:56.220 --> 00:29:58.720 align:middle line:90%
in the scriptures.

00:29:58.720 --> 00:30:01.660 align:middle line:84%
In the Old Testament,
the book of Numbers

00:30:01.660 --> 00:30:05.330 align:middle line:84%
tells us how Moses received
a holy command to make water

00:30:05.330 --> 00:30:07.510 align:middle line:84%
a spring forth from
a rock to slake

00:30:07.510 --> 00:30:09.610 align:middle line:84%
the thirst of the
children of Israel

00:30:09.610 --> 00:30:12.190 align:middle line:84%
who had followed
him into the desert

00:30:12.190 --> 00:30:14.920 align:middle line:84%
and who were turning against
him because they thought

00:30:14.920 --> 00:30:16.960 align:middle line:90%
they would die of thirst.

00:30:16.960 --> 00:30:20.620 align:middle line:84%
And so water was granted to
the man and to their animals,

00:30:20.620 --> 00:30:23.620 align:middle line:84%
but God then refused Moses
and his followers entry

00:30:23.620 --> 00:30:26.600 align:middle line:84%
into the promised land
because they had doubted him.

00:30:26.600 --> 00:30:36.820 align:middle line:90%


00:30:36.820 --> 00:30:39.790 align:middle line:84%
>> The story of Moses and the
rock takes place in an arid

00:30:39.790 --> 00:30:40.780 align:middle line:90%
landscape.

00:30:40.780 --> 00:30:44.050 align:middle line:84%
A place where water appears
out of nowhere, like a miracle.

00:30:44.050 --> 00:30:49.600 align:middle line:90%


00:30:49.600 --> 00:30:52.870 align:middle line:84%
Christianity, Judaism,
the religion of Islam

00:30:52.870 --> 00:30:55.248 align:middle line:84%
were all born in
such an environment.

00:30:55.248 --> 00:31:01.600 align:middle line:90%


00:31:01.600 --> 00:31:03.730 align:middle line:84%
Water obviously plays
an important role

00:31:03.730 --> 00:31:06.280 align:middle line:84%
in the three religions
mentioned in the Bible,

00:31:06.280 --> 00:31:08.123 align:middle line:84%
because it was a
major preoccupation

00:31:08.123 --> 00:31:09.415 align:middle line:90%
for the peoples of those lands.

00:31:09.415 --> 00:31:14.740 align:middle line:90%


00:31:14.740 --> 00:31:18.070 align:middle line:84%
For the wandering tribes, water
is synonymous with plenty,

00:31:18.070 --> 00:31:21.020 align:middle line:90%
even if transient.

00:31:21.020 --> 00:31:23.390 align:middle line:90%
It's the promise of a future.

00:31:23.390 --> 00:31:26.663 align:middle line:84%
A guarantee of the
herd's survival

00:31:26.663 --> 00:31:27.830 align:middle line:90%
of the future of the tribes.

00:31:27.830 --> 00:31:40.230 align:middle line:90%


00:31:40.230 --> 00:31:45.030 align:middle line:84%
>> In the Quran, water is
considered a gift from God.

00:31:45.030 --> 00:31:47.685 align:middle line:84%
Its virtues bear witness to
the existence of the prophet.

00:31:47.685 --> 00:31:51.720 align:middle line:90%


00:31:51.720 --> 00:31:55.290 align:middle line:84%
Endowed with positive powers,
it assumes a natural place

00:31:55.290 --> 00:31:56.790 align:middle line:90%
in symbolism and ritual.

00:31:56.790 --> 00:32:00.620 align:middle line:90%


00:32:00.620 --> 00:32:03.860 align:middle line:84%
For the Muslims, it's at the
center of daily practices.

00:32:03.860 --> 00:32:12.122 align:middle line:90%


00:32:12.122 --> 00:32:14.066 align:middle line:90%
[NON-ENGLISH SINGING]

00:32:14.066 --> 00:32:29.510 align:middle line:90%


00:32:29.510 --> 00:32:34.180 align:middle line:84%
Ablutions now an indispensable
preliminary to prayer.

00:32:34.180 --> 00:32:36.160 align:middle line:84%
But the origins of
the tradition were

00:32:36.160 --> 00:32:37.965 align:middle line:84%
rooted in a simple
concern for hygiene.

00:32:37.965 --> 00:32:43.370 align:middle line:90%


00:32:43.370 --> 00:32:46.700 align:middle line:84%
>> So the significance of
water has changed many times

00:32:46.700 --> 00:32:48.380 align:middle line:90%
throughout history.

00:32:48.380 --> 00:32:50.240 align:middle line:84%
It's strictly
profane use evolving

00:32:50.240 --> 00:32:52.344 align:middle line:90%
towards a sacred dimension.

00:32:52.344 --> 00:32:55.250 align:middle line:90%


00:32:55.250 --> 00:32:57.830 align:middle line:84%
We have an example of this
with the spread of Christianity

00:32:57.830 --> 00:33:00.240 align:middle line:84%
in the Mediterranean basin
towards the end of the Roman

00:33:00.240 --> 00:33:01.040 align:middle line:90%
Empire.

00:33:01.040 --> 00:33:07.880 align:middle line:90%


00:33:07.880 --> 00:33:10.940 align:middle line:84%
The Romans had a very strong
relationship with water,

00:33:10.940 --> 00:33:15.170 align:middle line:84%
although it was
rather a pagan one.

00:33:15.170 --> 00:33:18.050 align:middle line:84%
They had mastered the
technique of running water,

00:33:18.050 --> 00:33:21.210 align:middle line:84%
and often had it
installed in their houses.

00:33:21.210 --> 00:33:23.900 align:middle line:84%
They systematically constructed
baths in their cities

00:33:23.900 --> 00:33:25.340 align:middle line:84%
and in the colonies
they founded.

00:33:25.340 --> 00:33:30.570 align:middle line:90%


00:33:30.570 --> 00:33:34.380 align:middle line:84%
>> In Carthage, under the
reign of Emperor Antonin,

00:33:34.380 --> 00:33:37.350 align:middle line:84%
they built an important
complex of baths on the edge

00:33:37.350 --> 00:33:41.070 align:middle line:84%
of the sea, vestiges
of which still remain.

00:33:41.070 --> 00:33:42.790 align:middle line:90%
The baths of Antonin.

00:33:42.790 --> 00:33:45.780 align:middle line:84%
Today, only the
basement area remains.

00:33:45.780 --> 00:33:47.910 align:middle line:84%
The structure of the
vaulted rooms that

00:33:47.910 --> 00:33:49.590 align:middle line:90%
supported these gigantic baths.

00:33:49.590 --> 00:33:56.110 align:middle line:90%


00:33:56.110 --> 00:34:00.560 align:middle line:84%
The frigidarium rested on
eight columns like this.

00:34:00.560 --> 00:34:02.890 align:middle line:90%
They were about 15 meters high.

00:34:02.890 --> 00:34:05.200 align:middle line:84%
This gives us an idea of
the original dimensions

00:34:05.200 --> 00:34:07.070 align:middle line:90%
of the building.

00:34:07.070 --> 00:34:11.739 align:middle line:84%
It was one of the most important
structures in the city.

00:34:11.739 --> 00:34:14.690 align:middle line:84%
>> People went there for their
personal hygiene, of course,

00:34:14.690 --> 00:34:17.949 align:middle line:84%
but also for their well-being,
to enjoy themselves,

00:34:17.949 --> 00:34:20.739 align:middle line:90%
to meet people.

00:34:20.739 --> 00:34:22.810 align:middle line:84%
It was one of the
centers of social life.

00:34:22.810 --> 00:34:28.469 align:middle line:90%


00:34:28.469 --> 00:34:30.989 align:middle line:84%
Later, these strictly
pagan buildings

00:34:30.989 --> 00:34:33.462 align:middle line:84%
would be of great interest
to the Christians.

00:34:33.462 --> 00:34:38.550 align:middle line:90%


00:34:38.550 --> 00:34:40.739 align:middle line:84%
In the beginning of
our era, churches

00:34:40.739 --> 00:34:43.110 align:middle line:84%
were constructed in the
middle of Roman ruins

00:34:43.110 --> 00:34:44.610 align:middle line:90%
on the site of disused baths.

00:34:44.610 --> 00:34:47.370 align:middle line:90%


00:34:47.370 --> 00:34:49.980 align:middle line:84%
This was so as to make use
of the former installations

00:34:49.980 --> 00:34:52.259 align:middle line:84%
of running water for the
sacrament of baptism.

00:34:52.259 --> 00:34:55.260 align:middle line:90%


00:34:55.260 --> 00:34:58.240 align:middle line:84%
>> At Sufetula, to
the south of Carthage,

00:34:58.240 --> 00:35:01.620 align:middle line:84%
there are fine examples of funds
which were used for baptismal

00:35:01.620 --> 00:35:02.460 align:middle line:90%
ceremonies.

00:35:02.460 --> 00:35:08.791 align:middle line:90%


00:35:08.791 --> 00:35:10.739 align:middle line:90%
[VOCALIZING]

00:35:10.739 --> 00:35:19.040 align:middle line:90%


00:35:19.040 --> 00:35:22.100 align:middle line:84%
The emotion of the faithful,
originally performed

00:35:22.100 --> 00:35:24.950 align:middle line:84%
in natural surroundings,
could be carried out here.

00:35:24.950 --> 00:35:28.700 align:middle line:90%


00:35:28.700 --> 00:35:31.610 align:middle line:84%
Christ was baptized by John
the Baptist in the Jordan.

00:35:31.610 --> 00:35:37.020 align:middle line:90%


00:35:37.020 --> 00:35:39.960 align:middle line:84%
>> Baptismal
symbolism is strong.

00:35:39.960 --> 00:35:42.390 align:middle line:84%
In this ceremony,
water purifiers

00:35:42.390 --> 00:35:43.530 align:middle line:90%
to the point of death.

00:35:43.530 --> 00:35:46.220 align:middle line:90%


00:35:46.220 --> 00:35:51.170 align:middle line:84%
Any pagan who immerses himself
dies, and any man who comes out

00:35:51.170 --> 00:35:53.240 align:middle line:90%
of it is a new man.

00:35:53.240 --> 00:35:54.320 align:middle line:90%
A Christian.

00:35:54.320 --> 00:35:57.680 align:middle line:90%


00:35:57.680 --> 00:35:59.750 align:middle line:84%
It is not by chance
that the river was

00:35:59.750 --> 00:36:02.780 align:middle line:90%
the original site for baptism.

00:36:02.780 --> 00:36:07.220 align:middle line:84%
The river is an access of
life, a channel of fertility.

00:36:07.220 --> 00:36:09.540 align:middle line:84%
It enriches the
symbolic power of water.

00:36:09.540 --> 00:36:28.340 align:middle line:90%


00:36:28.340 --> 00:36:31.940 align:middle line:10%
>> When an entire people, an
entire civilization depends

00:36:31.940 --> 00:36:34.880 align:middle line:10%
on the benefits or the
winds of the river,

00:36:34.880 --> 00:36:38.300 align:middle line:10%
the river itself assumes all
the positive or negative powers

00:36:38.300 --> 00:36:41.390 align:middle line:10%
of water and takes on
its own sacred dimension.

00:36:41.390 --> 00:36:48.680 align:middle line:90%


00:36:48.680 --> 00:36:51.800 align:middle line:84%
It becomes inassociable
from the liquid element.

00:36:51.800 --> 00:36:58.970 align:middle line:84%
Blends into it like the Nile
in the Egyptian civilization.

00:36:58.970 --> 00:37:02.600 align:middle line:84%
>> The word Nile comes
from the Egyptian nwy,

00:37:02.600 --> 00:37:04.180 align:middle line:90%
the generic term for water.

00:37:04.180 --> 00:37:19.630 align:middle line:90%


00:37:19.630 --> 00:37:24.670 align:middle line:84%
Egypt owes everything to water
since the beginning of time.

00:37:24.670 --> 00:37:27.220 align:middle line:84%
Without it, the desert
would have remained barren.

00:37:27.220 --> 00:37:38.670 align:middle line:90%


00:37:38.670 --> 00:37:42.510 align:middle line:10%
Since the time of the pharaohs,
men have worked their shadufs

00:37:42.510 --> 00:37:44.880 align:middle line:10%
and drawn their water from
just beneath the surface

00:37:44.880 --> 00:37:45.680 align:middle line:10%
of the earth.

00:37:45.680 --> 00:37:48.680 align:middle line:90%


00:37:48.680 --> 00:37:51.290 align:middle line:84%
In ancient Egypt, it
was said that this water

00:37:51.290 --> 00:37:54.230 align:middle line:84%
was the perspiration
from the hands of Osiris,

00:37:54.230 --> 00:37:56.290 align:middle line:90%
god of fertility.

00:37:56.290 --> 00:37:59.810 align:middle line:84%
A life giving water, which
when the floods came,

00:37:59.810 --> 00:38:01.430 align:middle line:90%
deposited a fertile alluvium.

00:38:01.430 --> 00:38:07.620 align:middle line:90%


00:38:07.620 --> 00:38:09.990 align:middle line:84%
>> Ever since the Nile
was controlled upstream

00:38:09.990 --> 00:38:13.500 align:middle line:84%
by the Aswan Dam, the banks
of the river had never failed

00:38:13.500 --> 00:38:16.320 align:middle line:84%
to keep their promise of fine
harvest along the irrigated

00:38:16.320 --> 00:38:17.120 align:middle line:90%
strip.

00:38:17.120 --> 00:38:24.330 align:middle line:90%


00:38:24.330 --> 00:38:28.080 align:middle line:84%
By preventing the floods
and retaining the alluvium,

00:38:28.080 --> 00:38:30.810 align:middle line:84%
man has interfered with
the original reference.

00:38:30.810 --> 00:38:33.390 align:middle line:84%
The founding myth of
the beneficent river,

00:38:33.390 --> 00:38:34.395 align:middle line:90%
and yet, it remains.

00:38:34.395 --> 00:38:44.850 align:middle line:90%


00:38:44.850 --> 00:38:47.940 align:middle line:84%
>> Here, the Nile is
part of everyday life.

00:38:47.940 --> 00:38:50.490 align:middle line:90%
People live by it without fear.

00:38:50.490 --> 00:38:53.070 align:middle line:84%
Yet, no one ever thinks that
it has lost all its powers.

00:38:53.070 --> 00:38:58.650 align:middle line:90%


00:38:58.650 --> 00:39:01.350 align:middle line:84%
Its waters once incarnated
divine authority

00:39:01.350 --> 00:39:03.630 align:middle line:90%
in the land of men.

00:39:03.630 --> 00:39:05.915 align:middle line:84%
Those waters that held the
power of life and death

00:39:05.915 --> 00:39:06.715 align:middle line:90%
on their shores.

00:39:06.715 --> 00:39:09.240 align:middle line:90%


00:39:09.240 --> 00:39:11.220 align:middle line:84%
Today, the Egyptians
are still possessed

00:39:11.220 --> 00:39:16.160 align:middle line:84%
by that image of an all powerful
Nile of the Nile as a god.

00:39:16.160 --> 00:39:20.624 align:middle line:90%


00:39:20.624 --> 00:39:23.104 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:39:23.104 --> 00:39:35.520 align:middle line:90%


00:39:35.520 --> 00:39:38.700 align:middle line:84%
>> For many civilizations,
the river is the symbol

00:39:38.700 --> 00:39:43.130 align:middle line:84%
of crossing, of crossing
from one bank to the other.

00:39:43.130 --> 00:39:45.860 align:middle line:84%
In other words, it is a
passage from life to death.

00:39:45.860 --> 00:39:49.330 align:middle line:90%


00:39:49.330 --> 00:39:51.730 align:middle line:84%
This is doubtless one of
the places in the world

00:39:51.730 --> 00:39:53.980 align:middle line:84%
where this idea is
most strongly felt,

00:39:53.980 --> 00:39:56.800 align:middle line:84%
where it is most deeply rooted
in the collective memory.

00:39:56.800 --> 00:40:03.430 align:middle line:90%


00:40:03.430 --> 00:40:06.280 align:middle line:84%
>> Here, water has always
been the preferred medium

00:40:06.280 --> 00:40:09.430 align:middle line:84%
for traveling, in a literal
and figurative sense.

00:40:09.430 --> 00:40:20.830 align:middle line:90%


00:40:20.830 --> 00:40:22.670 align:middle line:10%
In the mythology
of the pharaohs,

00:40:22.670 --> 00:40:27.540 align:middle line:10%
the god Ra crosses the sky day
and night in his solar ship,

00:40:27.540 --> 00:40:30.680 align:middle line:10%
and the dead sailed the waters
in search of immortality.

00:40:30.680 --> 00:40:45.650 align:middle line:90%


00:40:45.650 --> 00:40:49.430 align:middle line:84%
The civilization of the Nile
validates the astonishing idea

00:40:49.430 --> 00:40:51.530 align:middle line:84%
of the philosopher
[INAUDIBLE],, who

00:40:51.530 --> 00:40:54.220 align:middle line:84%
said that the first of
all sailors was death.

00:40:54.220 --> 00:40:56.700 align:middle line:90%
[NON-ENGLISH SINGING]

00:40:56.700 --> 00:41:15.080 align:middle line:90%


00:41:15.080 --> 00:41:20.720 align:middle line:84%
>> The river flows
unpredictably, inexorably.

00:41:20.720 --> 00:41:22.790 align:middle line:84%
For a long time,
men knew neither

00:41:22.790 --> 00:41:26.100 align:middle line:84%
whence it came
nor where it went.

00:41:26.100 --> 00:41:29.350 align:middle line:84%
They often imagined that it
flowed away into the other life

00:41:29.350 --> 00:41:30.630 align:middle line:90%
through the land of the dead.

00:41:30.630 --> 00:41:38.200 align:middle line:90%


00:41:38.200 --> 00:41:40.630 align:middle line:84%
This idea was no
doubt reinforced

00:41:40.630 --> 00:41:43.840 align:middle line:84%
by the testimony of those who
had seen the waters disappear

00:41:43.840 --> 00:41:45.100 align:middle line:90%
into the bowels of the earth.

00:41:45.100 --> 00:41:49.690 align:middle line:90%


00:41:49.690 --> 00:41:52.660 align:middle line:84%
>> Homer said that all
rivers rose from and returned

00:41:52.660 --> 00:41:56.733 align:middle line:84%
to the [NON-ENGLISH],, an abyss
leading to the underworld.

00:41:56.733 --> 00:42:01.080 align:middle line:90%


00:42:01.080 --> 00:42:06.600 align:middle line:84%
In Greek mythology, there
were five rivers of hell.

00:42:06.600 --> 00:42:09.770 align:middle line:84%
And it was here that man
crossed over from life to death.

00:42:09.770 --> 00:42:15.380 align:middle line:90%


00:42:15.380 --> 00:42:18.860 align:middle line:90%
The Styx was the river of hate.

00:42:18.860 --> 00:42:22.980 align:middle line:84%
It circled the
underworld nine times.

00:42:22.980 --> 00:42:26.140 align:middle line:84%
Lethe was the river
of forgetfulness.

00:42:26.140 --> 00:42:31.480 align:middle line:84%
It made the souls of the dead
forget their life on Earth.

00:42:31.480 --> 00:42:35.180 align:middle line:84%
But to reach Elysium,
symbol of a new life,

00:42:35.180 --> 00:42:37.220 align:middle line:84%
they had first to
cross the Acheron.

00:42:37.220 --> 00:42:39.900 align:middle line:90%


00:42:39.900 --> 00:42:42.540 align:middle line:84%
To do this, the souls had
to deliver themselves up

00:42:42.540 --> 00:42:46.110 align:middle line:84%
to Charon, a sinister ferryman
who took them in his boat.

00:42:46.110 --> 00:42:50.390 align:middle line:90%


00:42:50.390 --> 00:42:52.910 align:middle line:10%
The crossing of the river
was the symbolic marking

00:42:52.910 --> 00:42:55.360 align:middle line:10%
of the great passing
over to the other side.

00:42:55.360 --> 00:42:59.190 align:middle line:90%


00:42:59.190 --> 00:43:02.940 align:middle line:84%
>> In the teachings of Japanese
Buddhism and of Shinto,

00:43:02.940 --> 00:43:07.200 align:middle line:84%
we find the same image of
the river, the Sanzu-no-kawa,

00:43:07.200 --> 00:43:09.890 align:middle line:84%
that separates the land of the
dead from that of the living.

00:43:09.890 --> 00:43:19.740 align:middle line:90%


00:43:19.740 --> 00:43:23.410 align:middle line:84%
If water is thus associated
with the mystery of death.

00:43:23.410 --> 00:43:25.650 align:middle line:84%
It is because water
itself is a mystery.

00:43:25.650 --> 00:43:28.420 align:middle line:90%


00:43:28.420 --> 00:43:34.210 align:middle line:84%
Its elusive body nourishes
the universal imagination.

00:43:34.210 --> 00:43:37.180 align:middle line:84%
>> In all civilizations, they
tell of how beneath the surface

00:43:37.180 --> 00:43:40.930 align:middle line:84%
of the water, another
world is inhabited.

00:43:40.930 --> 00:43:43.675 align:middle line:84%
It is the kingdom of strange
and temperamental powers.

00:43:43.675 --> 00:43:57.700 align:middle line:90%


00:43:57.700 --> 00:44:03.490 align:middle line:84%
In Norse mythology, the ocean
is ruled by unpredictable gods.

00:44:03.490 --> 00:44:07.270 align:middle line:84%
Sometimes harmful because they
are blamed for shipwrecks,

00:44:07.270 --> 00:44:10.270 align:middle line:84%
sometimes kindly because
they're providers of fish.

00:44:10.270 --> 00:44:12.536 align:middle line:90%
[NON-ENGLISH SINGING]

00:44:12.536 --> 00:44:23.530 align:middle line:90%


00:44:23.530 --> 00:44:27.640 align:middle line:84%
>> To every aspect of water,
there is a corresponding world,

00:44:27.640 --> 00:44:30.610 align:middle line:90%
beliefs, and myths.

00:44:30.610 --> 00:44:33.280 align:middle line:84%
For the Japanese,
supernatural creatures

00:44:33.280 --> 00:44:37.720 align:middle line:84%
called kappas live in rivers,
and these must be feared.

00:44:37.720 --> 00:44:39.880 align:middle line:84%
Just as the spirits
hiding behind the torrent

00:44:39.880 --> 00:44:41.442 align:middle line:90%
of a waterfall must be feared.

00:44:41.442 --> 00:44:52.540 align:middle line:90%


00:44:52.540 --> 00:44:55.690 align:middle line:84%
>> Waterfalls gave rise to
veritable cults in primitive

00:44:55.690 --> 00:44:57.240 align:middle line:90%
societies.

00:44:57.240 --> 00:44:58.870 align:middle line:84%
The people saw in
them the presence

00:44:58.870 --> 00:45:01.615 align:middle line:84%
of very powerful divinities
that had to be appeased.

00:45:01.615 --> 00:45:07.340 align:middle line:90%


00:45:07.340 --> 00:45:11.420 align:middle line:84%
Sometimes in South America and
Africa, animals and even men

00:45:11.420 --> 00:45:14.030 align:middle line:84%
were sacrificed to
them by being thrown

00:45:14.030 --> 00:45:15.170 align:middle line:90%
from the top of the fall.

00:45:15.170 --> 00:45:20.090 align:middle line:90%


00:45:20.090 --> 00:45:23.270 align:middle line:84%
However fearsome these
gods or spirits might be,

00:45:23.270 --> 00:45:27.560 align:middle line:84%
they are strictly localized
and their influence is slight,

00:45:27.560 --> 00:45:30.065 align:middle line:84%
being confined to the immediate
vicinity of the cascade.

00:45:30.065 --> 00:45:35.520 align:middle line:90%


00:45:35.520 --> 00:45:38.730 align:middle line:84%
In fact, there are few major
gods in the aquatic pantheon.

00:45:38.730 --> 00:45:42.620 align:middle line:90%


00:45:42.620 --> 00:45:46.480 align:middle line:10%
>> Only in ancient Greece do we
find a clearly identified god

00:45:46.480 --> 00:45:50.280 align:middle line:10%
reigning alone over the
waters of the world.

00:45:50.280 --> 00:45:51.920 align:middle line:10%
This is Poseidon.

00:45:51.920 --> 00:45:53.180 align:middle line:10%
The Romans called him Neptune.

00:45:53.180 --> 00:46:01.490 align:middle line:90%


00:46:01.490 --> 00:46:04.850 align:middle line:84%
Roaring up on his chariot,
he could provoke a storm

00:46:04.850 --> 00:46:06.890 align:middle line:84%
just by striking the
sea with his trident.

00:46:06.890 --> 00:46:10.320 align:middle line:90%


00:46:10.320 --> 00:46:14.440 align:middle line:10%
>> His powers were not
limited to the ocean.

00:46:14.440 --> 00:46:18.010 align:middle line:10%
He was also the god of
rivers, streams, and springs.

00:46:18.010 --> 00:46:21.190 align:middle line:90%


00:46:21.190 --> 00:46:24.430 align:middle line:84%
Consequently, he was the
master of the Naiads,

00:46:24.430 --> 00:46:27.490 align:middle line:84%
those nymphs, those wispy
divinities connected

00:46:27.490 --> 00:46:30.310 align:middle line:90%
with living waters.

00:46:30.310 --> 00:46:33.010 align:middle line:84%
They were as numerous as
there are trickles of water.

00:46:33.010 --> 00:46:40.330 align:middle line:90%


00:46:40.330 --> 00:46:43.360 align:middle line:84%
>> Spring water, with
its delicate song,

00:46:43.360 --> 00:46:46.760 align:middle line:84%
its limpid rhythm, tends to
be associated with kindly

00:46:46.760 --> 00:46:47.560 align:middle line:90%
divinities.

00:46:47.560 --> 00:46:50.390 align:middle line:90%


00:46:50.390 --> 00:46:54.070 align:middle line:84%
In Celtic tradition, this
water springing in the meadows

00:46:54.070 --> 00:46:56.780 align:middle line:84%
or bubbling up from the
foot of an oak or a megalith

00:46:56.780 --> 00:46:59.945 align:middle line:84%
in the forest is often
endowed with magic powers.

00:46:59.945 --> 00:47:08.020 align:middle line:90%


00:47:08.020 --> 00:47:12.280 align:middle line:84%
The Druids decided what powers
were possessed by springs

00:47:12.280 --> 00:47:14.850 align:middle line:84%
and the people were only too
ready to believe in them.

00:47:14.850 --> 00:47:20.500 align:middle line:90%


00:47:20.500 --> 00:47:23.410 align:middle line:84%
>> One type of water
brought fertility,

00:47:23.410 --> 00:47:27.110 align:middle line:90%
another cured headaches.

00:47:27.110 --> 00:47:31.070 align:middle line:84%
There were springs to protect
young girls and others

00:47:31.070 --> 00:47:33.020 align:middle line:90%
to give new vigor to old men.

00:47:33.020 --> 00:47:37.400 align:middle line:90%


00:47:37.400 --> 00:47:39.980 align:middle line:84%
These beliefs have been
given such credibility

00:47:39.980 --> 00:47:44.060 align:middle line:84%
that they have survived through
time and outlived paganism.

00:47:44.060 --> 00:47:52.320 align:middle line:90%


00:47:52.320 --> 00:47:55.170 align:middle line:84%
>> Religious authorities
feared the persistence of this

00:47:55.170 --> 00:47:58.290 align:middle line:84%
fascination, but they had
difficulty in destroying

00:47:58.290 --> 00:48:00.780 align:middle line:84%
the springs or preventing
access to them.

00:48:00.780 --> 00:48:11.860 align:middle line:90%


00:48:11.860 --> 00:48:14.670 align:middle line:84%
>> The church chose to ignore
the pagan origins of water

00:48:14.670 --> 00:48:18.660 align:middle line:84%
worship by systematically
imposing on fountains

00:48:18.660 --> 00:48:21.390 align:middle line:84%
the patronage of a
Christian protector,

00:48:21.390 --> 00:48:25.050 align:middle line:84%
a male or a female saint
with a beautiful story.

00:48:25.050 --> 00:48:29.571 align:middle line:90%
Like the story of St. Noyal

00:48:29.571 --> 00:48:33.880 align:middle line:84%
